<%#
  # Partial: _first_page.html.erb
  # Date: 11/20/2025
  # Author: MoisÃ©s Reis
  # Package: Kaminari
  #
  # Description: Renders a navigation link to the first page of the paginated resource list.
  #              It ensures the link is only active when the current page is not the first one.
  #
  # Usage: - What: Renders the control link for accessing the first page of a paginated data set.
  #                It is styled as a small outlined button with the label "Primeira".
  #        - How: Utilizes the Kaminari `link_to_unless` helper, which checks the
  #               `current_page.first?` status to disable the link when unnecessary.
  #               The link targets the provided `url` and respects the `remote` setting.
  #        - Why: Provides a quick, consistent, and intuitive mechanism for users
  #               to return to the start of a large paginated collection.
  %>
<span class="button button-outline button-small">
  <%= link_to_unless current_page.first?,
                     "Primeira".html_safe,
                     url, remote: remote
  %>
</span>
